# 1. If - Assign 5 to x. If x is bigger than 0, print "x is a positive number".

# 2. If-else - Assign -5 to y. If x is bigger than 0, print "x is a positive number". Else, print "x is a negative number".

# 3. If-elif-else - Assign 0 to z. If x is bigger than 0, print "x is a positive number". Else if x is zero, print "x is 0". Else, print "x is a negative number".

